{
  "text": "Ammann [CITATION_1] report that this enhancement factor is limited to mean flow rates (persons/s over the width of the deck) below 1.5 persons/s/m, whereas the flow rate for a density of 2.11 p/m 2 , given the distributions of pedestrian and crowd parameters in this work, is 2.6 p/s/m on average (the minimum is 1.6 p/s/m). Fig. 5(c) gives the results of DM 2 and it can be seen that regardless of the increase in crowd density, the enhancement factors remain similar due to the corresponding increase in damping.",
